There's someone fixing my kitchen floor right now, and I'm pretending to have a job while working from home, while I'm actually watching Too Hot to Handle.
If I could only manage to open the file. (Damn One Drive.)
*Voice of a hacker* I'm in.
And that's exactly when he starts drilling super loudly. Great.
It feels somewhat passive-aggressive to turn my air purifier to the max, but I can smell the wood dust, so it would be fine even if he wasn't anti-mask, and must I really protect myself?
I would really like to go back to bed, but I can't, before he leaves.
At least I've finally finished revising chapter 4!
Chapter 5 is long, but so damn terrifying. Oh yes, that's the good stuff!
I'm doing Find and Replace for … ➡️ Ellipses symbol and there are 54 in this chapter 😅
But no, I'm sticking to it. Natural language is often disjointed, especially when you get emotional.
The handyman is now busy with the vacuum cleaner. Hopefully, that means he will be done soon.
He went out to cut something (sounds like that anyway). I looked in secretly to see how far he's gotten. There's still a lot to do :((
Still 7 pages left in Chapter 5. Still my favorite chapter and it's quite tidy – mainly changes to the font and very small corrections in direct speech and I have to rephrase everything a bit more compactly. But I really need a break and a cup of tea, but the guy is still in my kitchen.
Now he's started vacuuming again. Hopefully, that's a good sign.
The guy in the kitchen is gone!
He told me that he had made an estimate for the entire floor, but the landlords were too stingy and only paid for the part next to the door, which is no longer in order. Feels just as good.
The house is being ventilated and in the kitchen my air purifier is running, while I'm drinking tea in the garden!
